  "description": [
    "U S Policy of Terror in Korea An oppressed Japanese colony for 40 years Korea is now be ing treated worse than most oc cupied enemy countries by the United States military govern ment So the STAR learned this week in a firsthand report from an American soldier sta tioned in Korea from the begin ning of the American occupa tion last September Former Technical Sergeant Daniel L Zinn returned to ci vilian life at Fort Sheridan last week described the bitter con trast between the attitude of the Korean people to the American Gls when they first landed and their present feeling toward U S troops WHEN WE first arrived in Korea we were overwhelmed with welcomes gifts and gener al enthusiasm Things have got to the point now where Ameri can soldiers have to go out on the buddy system two at a time for selfprotection There are no black markets in Korea said Zinn because the AMG has adopted the simple Anglo American bloc stymies peace parley PARIS lnsistence by the Soviet Union on Big Four unity and that the recent agree ments between the foreign ministers of England France America and Russia be lived up to"
  ],
